{
  "stem": "1169.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it seems that he made a deal with this Eichmann, [SPEAKING HEBREW] may his name be erased, that he would let 1,850 Jews out of Hungary for $5 million.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, he offered to let all the Hungarian Jews free for money and trucks and coffee, for all types of goodies.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But this deal was made definite, and as my aunt told me the story that Kastner came in one day to the office of the Zionist movement.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And he said he can save now 1,850 Jews and please give me names.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Whoever has names, put it on the list.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He also said, and I want to emphasize this specifically, that he wants to save-- this is a Talmudic expression called [SPEAKING HEBREW] which refers to the students and the scholars.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "He wanted to save as many of the sages of Hungary, as possible.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And that's why they put on this list also the very holy Rabbi of Satu Mare of blessed memory, and Rabbi Steif, who was the head of the [INAUDIBLE] of Hungary, and also many Rabbis.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I don't remember all their names.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I remember one other very famous rabbi at the time, was name of-- his name was Rabbi Strasser.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He was a gentleman who was 87 years old at the time-- a tall gentleman, a beautiful gentlemen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He was the Rabbi of Debrecen, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the last Rabbi of Debrecen, and many others.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "My aunt put all the Rabbi Jungreises on this list, as many as she could, and of course her parents-- My grandfather was the Rabbi of [HUNGARIAN]-- and all the uncles and cousins, but it was too late.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They were already deported.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
